        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 16 at 12:39PM EDT by NWS Detroit/Pontiac MI</headline>
        <description>At 1238 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms near Milford, moving northeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Troy, Pontiac, Novi, Milford, Holly, Oxford, Royal Oak, Birmingham,
Rochester, South Lyon, Ortonville, Clarkston, West Bloomfield,
Farmington Hills, Rochester Hills, Auburn Hills, Wixom, Clawson,
Beverly Hills, and Walled Lake.

People attending Oakland County Fair  should seek safe shelter
immediately!
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
